## Stage: neat-memory surfacing

**Verdict: working.** The curator reads observations and retros, judges candidates, sends only on selected high-signal items, records sent state, and schedules the next beat.

What writes:

- On `--apply`, if the decision is `send`, `neat-memory.ts` sends `joelclaw notify send --priority low --source observer/neat-memory ...` and writes `/Users/joel/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json` only after the send envelope is ok. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory.ts:98-105` and `125-137`.
- `bin/neat-memory.sh` schedules the next beat with `joelclaw wake in <nextBeat> --verb spawn --brief ...`; the daily LaunchAgent is the dead-man. Receipt: `~/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw-observer/bin/neat-memory.sh` and live plist path `/Users/joel/.joelclaw/observer-release/bin/neat-memory.sh`.

What reads:

- Candidate files come from observations and retros. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory.ts:108-112`.
- The judge prompt includes recent send history and compact candidate excerpts. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory.ts:61-70`.
- Candidate links are 200-checked against `https://brain.joelclaw.com/user/observations/<slug>` or `https://brain.joelclaw.com/resources/retros/<slug>` before using the canonical URL; otherwise the file path is used. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/neat-memory.ts:90-96`.

Where state lives:

- State file: `/Users/joel/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json`, version `1`, `sent: 6`, mtime `2026-07-17T16:20:54Z`.
- Log file: `/tmp/observer-neat-memory.log`.

Receipts:

- `/tmp/observer-neat-memory.log` shows a beat at `2026-07-17T10:19:41Z`, `check complete`, next beat scheduled in `6h` as `f5a6e6da-2e0b-48a2-9b7c-4498730f975e`.
- It then shows a beat at `2026-07-17T16:20:35Z`, `check complete`, next beat scheduled in `12h` as `9783956b-52e3-45c0-8b67-b2c8ab05b45d`.
- State shows the latest send: slug `2026-07-17-777a1698e894`, sent at `2026-07-17T16:20:35.058Z`, score `8.6`, flavor `milestone-win`, model `openai-codex/gpt-5.6-sol:xhigh`.

## Stage: self-maintenance tick

**Verdict: wobbly.** Tick v4 is alive and checking itself, but the self-reflection write path is still staged and one warning repeats every tick.

What writes:

- The tick supervisor calls self-maintenance with `--apply` before sending the observer `tick`. Receipt: `/Users/joel/.joelclaw/bin/observer-tick.sh:281-303`.
- `self-maintenance.ts --apply` writes only its own log and pane-gardening actions. It builds and validates a self-reflection page, but returns `writePolicy: "staged only; steering installs observation write path"`. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/self-maintenance.ts:135-145`.

What reads:

- Self-maintenance reads family registry, dispatcher pane, tick log, dispatcher dedupe, telemetry state, pending publish state, observer/dream/context launch logs, current panes, and observation counts. Receipt: `~/.joelclaw/observer-release/.pi/extensions/observer/self-maintenance.ts:115-133`.

Where state lives:

- Self-maintenance log: `/tmp/observer-self-maintenance.log`.
- Tick log: `/tmp/observer-tick.log`.
- Family and state files under `/Users/joel/.joelclaw/`.

Receipts:

- `/tmp/observer-tick.log` says `2026-07-17T16:26:33Z tick sent pane=w4:p2A`.
- The same tick's self-check marked `family-registry`, `dispatcher-dedupe`, `telemetry-state`, `pending-state`, `unpublished-backlog`, `observer-tick`, and `observer-dream` as ok.
- The same tick warned: `launchagent:com.joelclaw.observer-context: com.joelclaw.observer-context log missing`.
- The same tick built and validated slug `2026-07-17-observer-self-reflection` but did not write it, because `writePolicy` is `staged only; steering installs observation write path`.
- `/tmp/observer-self-maintenance.log` shows repeated pane label gardening. The latest line is `2026-07-17T16:26:33.090Z gardening rename pane=w4:p8 label="📡 Dispatcher" reason=protected dispatcher label drift code=0`.

## Three load-bearing risks

1. **The dream cap can starve older pages after the first 200 sorted filenames.** The concern is not causing today's zero eligible pages, but the code really does slice to 200 before eligibility. With `652` top-level pages and `capped:true` already in the daily log, this becomes dangerous as soon as post-cap pages age past the threshold.
2. **Self-maintenance can see problems but cannot yet write its own durable observation.** It validates self-reflection pages every tick, and it is currently noisy enough to want to write, but the result stays in `/tmp/observer-tick.log` instead of the observation substrate.
3. **Retros are not part of the observer write loop.** Neat-memory consumes retros, but this survey found only 2 retro files and no observer-side retro writer. If retros are supposed to be first-class memory, they are currently a manual/adjacent input, not a pipeline stage.
